<p class="">No; the naval holiday simply meant that in the programmes of Germany and England, one year should be dropped out, one year should be a blank year.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-a8f40d9a-5c49-41a9-ab0f-5d61323ab4ea" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1939-03-16/debates/f40b7ab7-e4d7-4b7f-b629-3178761d0294/NavyEstimates1939#contribution-a8f40d9a-5c49-41a9-ab0f-5d61323ab4ea">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
